BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (How to Use This Tutorial) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (This tutorial is written for students who are learning to use GitHub Copilot as a programming) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (assistant inside Visual Studio Code. The goal is not to make Copilot do your homework for you. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 691.6 Td (goal is to learn how to ask better questions, read generated code critically, plan before coding,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 678.4 Td (and use AI support without giving up responsibility for the final work.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 661.2 Td (You should read this document with VS Code open. Try the shortcuts, ask the prompts, and compare) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 648 Td (Copilot's answers against your course notes, compiler errors, tests, and documentation. Copilot can) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 634.8 Td (be very helpful, but it can also be confidently wrong. Treat it as a fast pair programmer, not as an) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 621.6 Td (authority.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 604.4 Td (This tutorial focuses on five habits:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 587.2 Td (- Start with a plan before asking for code.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 574 Td (- Give Copilot enough context to understand the task.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 560.8 Td (- Choose the right mode for the job: Ask, Edit, Agent, or planning.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 547.6 Td (- Choose the right model size for the job.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 534.4 Td (- Verify every important answer with tests, reasoning, and review.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 521.2 Td (The examples use Windows and Linux keyboard shortcuts. On macOS, Ctrl is often replaced by Command,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 508 Td (and some shortcuts differ. If a shortcut does not work, open the Command Palette with Ctrl+Shift+P) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 494.8 Td (and search for the command by name.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 477.6 Td (By the end, you should be able to:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 460.4 Td (- Open and use Copilot Chat in VS Code.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 447.2 Td (- Use Ctrl+Shift+P to find commands quickly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 434 Td (- Use Ctrl+Shift+I and inline editing to work directly inside a file.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 420.8 Td (- Explain Ask mode, Edit mode, Agent mode, and plan-first workflows.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 407.6 Td (- Select models based on task difficulty and cost.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 394.4 Td (- Write prompts with context, instructions, and guardrails.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 381.2 Td (- Add repository instructions in .github/copilot-instructions.md.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 368 Td (- Understand how MCP servers and agent skills can provide extra context and tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 354.8 Td (The most important idea is simple: planning is part of programming. Do not save planning for large) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 341.6 Td (projects only. Even a short programming problem benefits from a clear plan, assumptions, inputs,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 328.4 Td (outputs, and tests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  2) Tj ET
endstream
