BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (4. Copilot Chat and Ctrl+Shift+I) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Copilot Chat is the main place to ask questions, request explanations, and work through tasks. In VS) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (Code, you can use chat in several ways:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 687.6 Td (- Chat view: a panel or sidebar conversation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 674.4 Td (- Quick chat: a small prompt box for fast questions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 661.2 Td (- Inline chat: a prompt directly in the editor.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 648 Td (- Smart actions: context menu actions such as explain, fix, or generate tests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 634.8 Td (Ctrl+Shift+I is commonly used to start inline Copilot Chat in the editor. Inline chat is useful when) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 621.6 Td (you want Copilot to focus on the current file or selected code. If that shortcut does not work in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 608.4 Td (your setup, use Ctrl+Shift+P and search for inline chat or Copilot inline commands.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 591.2 Td (Use inline chat when:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 574 Td (- You selected a block of code and want it explained.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 560.8 Td (- You want a small edit in one place.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 547.6 Td (- You want to ask about an error near the cursor.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 534.4 Td (- You want Copilot to rewrite a function without leaving the editor.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 521.2 Td (Example inline prompt:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 501 Td (Explain what this function does in plain English. Then identify one possible edge case. Do not) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 489 Td (    edit the file.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 474 Td (Example inline edit prompt:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 453.8 Td (Refactor this function to use early returns. Keep the same behavior. Do not rename public) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 441.8 Td (    functions. Add no new dependencies.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 426.8 Td (Inline chat is not the best place for broad architecture decisions. Use the full Chat view for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 413.6 Td (larger conversations because it is easier to keep track of context, plans, and follow-up questions.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 391.4 Td (Selection Matters) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 365.4 Td (When using inline chat, select the smallest relevant code region. If you select too little, Copilot) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 352.2 Td (may miss important dependencies. If you select too much, it may make broad edits. For a bug in one) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 339 Td (function, select the function. For a bug involving two functions, select both or reference the file) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 325.8 Td (names in chat.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  6) Tj ET
endstream
