24 0 obj
<< /Length 2981 >>
stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (8. Agent Mode) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Agent mode is for multi-step tasks. In agentic workflows, Copilot can inspect files, decide an) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (approach, propose edits, and sometimes use tools such as terminal commands, tests, or MCP tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 691.6 Td (Depending on your setup and policies, it may ask for confirmation before running commands or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 678.4 Td (applying changes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 661.2 Td (Use Agent mode when:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 644 Td (- The task spans multiple files.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 630.8 Td (- The implementation requires exploration.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 617.6 Td (- You want Copilot to run or interpret tests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 604.4 Td (- You need a coordinated refactor.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 591.2 Td (- You want a bug investigated from symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 578 Td (- You need generated code plus validation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 564.8 Td (Do not use Agent mode for every small question. It is more powerful, but also easier to over-scope.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 551.6 Td (If you only need an explanation, use Ask mode. If you need one function changed, use Edit mode. If) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 538.4 Td (you need a multi-file investigation, use Agent mode.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 521.2 Td (Good Agent mode prompt:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 501 Td (Investigate why the checkout tests are failing. First inspect the relevant tests and) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 489 Td (    implementation. Then propose a plan before editing. Do not change public APIs unless the) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 477 Td (    tests require it. After edits, run the smallest relevant test command and summarize the) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 465 Td (    result.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 450 Td (Agent mode should still be supervised. Read its plan. Watch which files it opens. Check commands) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 436.8 Td (before approving them. Review the final diff.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 414.6 Td (Agent Mode Risks) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 388.6 Td (Agent mode can make confident but broad changes. It may fix the symptom while weakening design,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 375.4 Td (remove tests instead of fixing code, or introduce dependencies that are not allowed. Guardrails) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 362.2 Td (matter more as autonomy increases.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 345 Td (Good guardrails:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 327.8 Td (- "Do not delete tests.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 314.6 Td (- "Do not add dependencies.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 301.4 Td (- "Use the existing project style.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 288.2 Td (- "Stop and ask before changing database schema.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 275 Td (- "Make the smallest change that fixes the failing test.") Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 261.8 Td (- "Show a plan and wait before editing.") Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  10) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
