stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (9. Plan Mode and Plan-First Work) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Plan mode means using Copilot to reason about the approach before writing code. Some Copilot) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (surfaces provide a plan-oriented workflow directly. Even when there is no separate button labeled) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 691.6 Td (Plan, you can create a plan-first workflow by prompting for a plan and telling Copilot not to edit) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 678.4 Td (yet.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 661.2 Td (Planning is the most important part of writing code because it determines what problem you are) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 648 Td (solving. A weak plan leads to wasted implementation. A strong plan makes coding faster, testing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 634.8 Td (clearer, and review easier.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 617.6 Td (Use planning for:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 600.4 Td (- Assignments with ambiguous requirements.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 587.2 Td (- Multi-file features.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 574 Td (- Debugging unfamiliar code.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 560.8 Td (- Refactors.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 547.6 Td (- Database changes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 534.4 Td (- API design.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 521.2 Td (- Security-sensitive work.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 508 Td (- Any task where a wrong direction would be expensive.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 494.8 Td (Planning prompt:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 474.6 Td (Before writing code, create a plan for implementing this assignment. Include assumptions, files) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 462.6 Td (    likely to change, edge cases, and tests. Ask clarifying questions if requirements are) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 450.6 Td (    missing. Do not edit files yet.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 435.6 Td (A good plan should include:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 418.4 Td (- Goal.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 405.2 Td (- Current understanding.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 392 Td (- Assumptions.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 378.8 Td (- Proposed file changes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 365.6 Td (- Data flow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 352.4 Td (- Edge cases.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 339.2 Td (- Test plan.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 326 Td (- Risks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 312.8 Td (- Checkpoints.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 299.6 Td (Planning is not wasted time. It is how you reduce rework.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 277.4 Td (Classroom Planning Standard) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 251.4 Td (Before using Agent mode for an assignment, write or request a plan. Then revise it. If the plan does) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 238.2 Td (not mention tests, edge cases, or constraints, it is not done.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 221 Td (For major tasks, use a large model for planning. The extra reasoning quality matters because) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 207.8 Td (mistakes in the plan cascade into every later step.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  11) Tj ET
endstream
