stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (10. Which Model Should You Select?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Copilot offers multiple models, and the available list changes over time by plan, IDE, organization) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (policy, and product rollout. Do not memorize a single permanent list. Instead, learn a selection) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 691.6 Td (strategy.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 674.4 Td (This course recommends a size-by-task rule:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 657.2 Td (- Small models for asking.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 644 Td (- Medium models for writing code.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 630.8 Td (- Large models for planning and hard reasoning.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 617.6 Td (Why?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 600.4 Td (Small models are usually fast and economical. They are good for direct questions, syntax help,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 587.2 Td (simple explanations, quick examples, and summarizing a short file.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 570 Td (Medium models are a good default for normal implementation. They can write code, follow project) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 556.8 Td (style, and handle moderate context without using the highest-cost option.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 539.6 Td (Large models should be saved for planning, architecture, debugging hard failures, security review,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 526.4 Td (and multi-step reasoning. Planning deserves the strongest model because it shapes the whole) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 513.2 Td (solution. A weak implementation can be corrected locally; a weak plan can send the entire project in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 500 Td (the wrong direction.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 477.8 Td (Practical Mapping) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 451.8 Td (Use a small model when asking:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 431.6 Td (What does this Python error mean?) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 419.6 Td (Explain the difference between a list and a tuple.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 407.6 Td (Show a tiny example of a SQL join.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 392.6 Td (Use a medium model when coding:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 372.4 Td (Implement this helper function using the existing style.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 360.4 Td (Write unit tests for this module.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 348.4 Td (Refactor this function without changing behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 333.4 Td (Use a large model when planning:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 313.2 Td (Design a plan to add authentication to this app.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 301.2 Td (Analyze this failing integration test and propose likely causes.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 289.2 Td (Review this architecture for security and maintainability risks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 274.2 Td (If your organization offers auto model selection, it may choose a model for you. Even then,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 261 Td (understand the tradeoff. Bigger is not always better. The right model is the smallest one that can) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 247.8 Td (do the job well.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  12) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
