stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (15. Repository Instructions: .github/copilot-instructions.md) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Repository instructions are persistent guidance stored in the repository. In VS Code and GitHub, a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (common file is:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 684.6 Td (.github/copilot-instructions.md) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 669.6 Td (This file tells Copilot how to behave when working in the project. It is useful because students) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 656.4 Td (otherwise repeat the same constraints in every prompt.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 639.2 Td (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 619 Td (# Copilot Instructions) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 607 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 595 Td (- Use Python 3.12 syntax unless the assignment says otherwise.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 583 Td (- Prefer clear beginner-readable code over clever one-liners.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 571 Td (- Do not add third-party dependencies without asking.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 559 Td (- Preserve public function signatures used by tests.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 547 Td (- When changing behavior, add or update unit tests.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 535 Td (- Do not remove failing tests to make the suite pass.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 523 Td (- Explain assumptions before making broad edits.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 508 Td (Good repository instructions are short, specific, and stable. Do not put the entire assignment in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 494.8 Td (this file if it changes every week. Put durable project rules there.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 477.6 Td (Path-specific instructions may also be supported through files such as:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 457.4 Td (.github/instructions/python.instructions.md) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 445.4 Td (.github/instructions/tests.instructions.md) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 430.4 Td (These can guide Copilot differently for application code and tests. For example, test instructions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 417.2 Td (might say to use pytest, avoid sleeps, and prefer deterministic fixtures.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 395 Td (What Not to Put in Instructions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 369 Td (Do not put secrets, passwords, API keys, private student information, or temporary debugging notes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 355.8 Td (in repository instructions. They are project files and may be committed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 338.6 Td (Also avoid contradictory instructions. If one instruction says "always write detailed comments" and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 325.4 Td (another says "avoid comments," Copilot may behave inconsistently.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  17) Tj ET
endstream
