stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (16. MCP Servers and Agent Skills) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (MCP stands for Model Context Protocol. It is an open standard for connecting AI tools to external) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 704.8 Td (context and capabilities. In Copilot, MCP servers can provide tools or resources that Copilot can) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 691.6 Td (use, especially in Agent mode.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 674.4 Td (Examples of what MCP servers can expose:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 657.2 Td (- Repository or issue data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 644 Td (- Browser or web-fetching tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 630.8 Td (- Database inspection tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 617.6 Td (- Documentation search.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 604.4 Td (- Internal APIs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 591.2 Td (- File or project resources.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 578 Td (- Testing or automation tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 564.8 Td (Think of MCP as a structured way to give Copilot safe access to tools beyond the text you type.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 551.6 Td (Instead of pasting a database schema into chat, a configured MCP server might provide schema) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 538.4 Td (context. Instead of manually copying issue details, a GitHub MCP server might expose issue and pull) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 525.2 Td (request data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 508 Td (Agent skills are reusable instructions or capabilities that guide agent behavior for a domain. A) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 494.8 Td (skill might teach an agent how to run a project, follow a deployment process, review accessibility,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 481.6 Td (or use a team-specific checklist.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 464.4 Td (For students, the key idea is:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 447.2 Td (- Custom instructions tell Copilot how to behave.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 434 Td (- MCP servers give Copilot additional context or tools.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 420.8 Td (- Skills package specialized workflows.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 402.6 Td (Safety With MCP) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 376.6 Td (Tools increase power and risk. Before allowing an MCP tool or agent action, ask:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 359.4 Td (- What data can this tool read?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 346.2 Td (- What can it write or change?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 333 Td (- Does it require secrets?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 319.8 Td (- Is it approved for this course or organization?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 306.6 Td (- Can I inspect what it did afterward?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 293.4 Td (Use only MCP servers your instructor or organization approves. A tool-connected assistant should be) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 280.2 Td (treated like a developer with access, not like a harmless autocomplete box.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  18) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
