stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (18. Debugging With Copilot) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Debugging is one of the best uses of Copilot, but only if you provide evidence.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 700.8 Td (A good debugging prompt includes:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 683.6 Td (- Expected behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 670.4 Td (- Actual behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 657.2 Td (- Exact error message.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 644 Td (- Relevant input.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 630.8 Td (- Relevant files or function names.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 617.6 Td (- What you already tried.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 604.4 Td (- Whether you want explanation, plan, or edits.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 591.2 Td (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 571 Td (Expected: `parse_date\("2026-06-26"\)` returns a date object.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 559 Td (Actual: it raises `ValueError: time data does not match format`.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 547 Td (Relevant file: `src/dates.py`.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 535 Td (I already checked that the input is a string.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 523 Td (Explain the likely cause and suggest one minimal fix. Do not edit yet.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 508 Td (Ask Copilot to form hypotheses before editing. This keeps debugging from turning into random) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 494.8 Td (changes.) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 474.6 Td (List three possible causes ranked by likelihood. For each, tell me what evidence would confirm) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 462.6 Td (    or disprove it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 447.6 Td (Then inspect the evidence. This is how professional debugging works: hypothesis, evidence,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 434.4 Td (experiment, conclusion.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 412.2 Td (Do Not Let Copilot Hide the Bug) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 386.2 Td (A bad AI fix may catch every exception and return a default value. That can make tests pass while) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 373 Td (hiding real errors. Guard against this:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 352.8 Td (Do not silence exceptions unless the assignment explicitly requires it. Prefer fixing the root) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 340.8 Td (    cause.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 325.8 Td (After a fix, run the smallest relevant test first, then the full suite. If no tests exist, ask) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 312.6 Td (Copilot to help design tests before trusting the fix.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  20) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
45 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 2 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 3 0 R /F2 4 0 R /F3 5 0 R >> >> /Contents 44 0 R >>
endobj
46 0 obj
<< /Length 2325 >>
stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (19. Testing With Copilot) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 718 Td (Copilot can help write tests, but you must decide what behavior matters.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 700.8 Td (Good test prompt:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 680.6 Td (Write pytest tests for `calculate_total`. Cover empty cart, inactive items, discount after tax,) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 668.6 Td (    and invalid negative prices. Use the existing test style. Do not change production code.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 653.6 Td (Weak test prompt:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 633.4 Td (Write tests.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 618.4 Td (Strong tests include normal cases, edge cases, and failure cases. Copilot often writes happy-path) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 605.2 Td (tests first. Push it further.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 588 Td (Ask:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 567.8 Td (What edge cases are missing from these tests?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 552.8 Td (or:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 532.6 Td (Review these tests. Are they testing behavior or only implementation details?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 517.6 Td (Students should learn the difference between:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 500.4 Td (- Testing that code runs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 487.2 Td (- Testing that code is correct.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 474 Td (- Testing that code handles edge cases.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 460.8 Td (- Testing that code fails safely.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 442.6 Td (Test-First Prompt) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 416.6 Td (For some assignments, start with tests:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 396.4 Td (Based on this requirement, propose test cases before implementation. Do not write production) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 384.4 Td (    code. Include expected inputs and outputs.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 369.4 Td (This is another form of planning. If you cannot describe tests, you probably do not understand the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 356.2 Td (requirement yet.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 334 Td (Never Remove Tests Casually) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 308 Td (If Copilot suggests deleting or weakening a failing test, stop. Ask:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 287.8 Td (Explain why this test is wrong according to the requirements. If it is valid, fix the) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 275.8 Td (    implementation instead.) Tj ET
BT /F1 8 Tf 54 30 Td (GitHub Copilot Tutorial for Students  |  21) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
