stream
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 744 Td (21. Common Mistakes) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 713 Td (Mistake 1: Asking Vague Questions) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 687 Td ("Fix my code" gives Copilot too much freedom. Name the file, function, expected behavior, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 673.8 Td (constraints.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 651.6 Td (Mistake 2: Skipping the Plan) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 625.6 Td (Students often jump into code because code feels productive. Planning prevents wasted effort. Use) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 612.4 Td (large models for planning when the task matters.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 590.2 Td (Mistake 3: Accepting Large Diffs) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 564.2 Td (A huge diff is hard to review. Ask for smaller changes:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 544 Td (Make only the smallest change needed for this test. Do not refactor unrelated code.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 524 Td (Mistake 4: Trusting Explanations Without Running Code) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 498 Td (Copilot can explain code that does not compile. Always run tests or execute examples.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 475.8 Td (Mistake 5: Letting Copilot Change the Assignment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 449.8 Td (If the assignment says no third-party libraries, do not accept a solution that adds one. If it) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 436.6 Td (requires recursion, do not accept a loop-only solution unless the instructor permits it.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 414.4 Td (Mistake 6: Hiding Lack of Understanding) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 388.4 Td (If you cannot explain the code, ask Copilot to teach:) Tj ET
BT /F3 9.5 Tf 54 368.2 Td (Explain this solution line by line and then quiz me.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 348.2 Td (Mistake 7: Using Agent Mode Without Guardrails) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 54 322.2 Td (Agent mode needs boundaries. Tell it what files not to touch, what tests to run, and when to stop.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 300 Td (Mistake 8: Confusing More Context With Better Context) Tj ET
